 Partnering with Live Services; service integration, service operations and service management teams to support end to end service operations across the supply chain
 Acting as a technical design analyst for mainframe infrastructure components
 Strong knowledge of IBM z-Enterprise server hardware
 Strong statistical and analytical skills, have a complete understanding of mainframe capacity planning concepts and be able to support capacity forecasting
 Strong Knowledge of mainframe application lifecycle management process, this includes source code management and release management
 Skilled in supporting user exits. A good working knowledge of High Level Assembler language is ideal
 Strong interpersonal skills, communications skills, and ability to work as a team member are essential
 Ability to use MS Office Software Products such as Visio, Project, Word, PowerPoint and Excel proficiently
 Detail oriented
 Proven ability to work creatively and analytically in a problem-solving environment
 Aggressive problem diagnosis and creative problem solving skills on highly complex problems; technical agility; project planning skills; ability to put together engineering designs and solid business / technical proposals
 Provide input to management on infrastructure opportunities
 Work with application developers and support groups to resolve issues and problems with infra subsystems
 Work with vendors and technical support teams to identify infra related problems
 Develop scripting to automate common system tasks/actions, alerts and problem tickets
 Develop wellness health check scripts, processes, and procedures (eg, new subsystem builds, maintenance implementations)
 Conduct Production Readiness Inspections of change events, assessing impacts and risks
 Provide technical recommendations involving environments and tools upon request
 Implementation of maintenance software product packages (OEM) provided by the Engineering team
 Monitor system resources, make tuning recommendations
 Manage service level of mainframe system and tracking problem management on mainframe issue
 Perform review of system changes, processes and routine system monitoring
 Monitor emerging technology trends related to the mainframe computing environment; Recommend adoption of new technologies/methodologies when appropriate
 Design, build and operate emerging mainframe technologies and processes
Qualifications
 At least 2 years of working experience in mainframe infrastructure build and administration
 Specialization in z/OS, Mainframe network OR in two or more of the following: Automated Operations Software, Enterprise Storage and related software, and MQSeries
 Two years of experience as primary system support and completed full-cycle of system implementation or upgrade